Introduction

Hello, my name is Ethan Wang-So. I am a student, programmer, and web designer. I am currently a second year student, majoring in Computer Science, at the New Jersey Institute of Technology. I have had a strong interest in software and coding since I was in high school. I took part in a school programming competition, where my team and I worked on an eye-tracking browser extension.



Currently, I work as a classroom assistant for the Computer Science Department at the New Jersey Institute of Technology. I am also involved with research in the MIXR Lab, which is a Virtual Reality facility on campus. In addition, I take part in clubs and organizations such as Association for Computing Machinery and Filipinos In Newark Engaging In Socio-Cultural Traditions.

You can read more below.



I am looking for any internship or co-op opportunities in the field of software engineering/development and computer science. I currently live in the New York/New Jersey area, but I am always willing to travel for a job.

Education

New Jersey Institute of Technology

GPA: 3.5

  • Bachelor of Science in Computer Science
  • Academic Excellence Scholarship Recipient
  • Dean's List

Skills & Experience

I am knowledgeable in several programming languages such as Python, Java, C#, C++, PHP, and Javascript. I am also well versed in frameworks and libraries such as Django and React. As mentioned under the Education section, I work as a Teacher's Assistant in the computer science department. I mainly assist in teaching Python to first year students.
